point.synopsis:
Sister's divorce. Men and women could be much freer with each other at dances and
               parties in Canada, because the boundaries were set by the permanence of marriage;
               in America you couldn't be friendly with an unmarried person.

point.title:
Advantages to women for sticking out marriage; being able to outmaneuver husband;
               women's strength; the toleration of bad and unfaithful husbands but not unfaithful
               women
